#4

2 cups flour
1 tbl baking powder
1 tsp salt
1 tbl sugar
-Whisk it all up- then add..
1 tsp vanilla
1 1/2 c 30% whipping cream

Roll out the dough. Should make 10 3" round biscuits.

2..3 tbl melted butter (brush on top before n after cooking)

Bake (foil lined pan) at 425, 11 minutes?

-----------------

Original

2 cups flour
1 tbl baking powder
1 tsp salt
1 tbl sugar
1 1/2 c whipping cream

2..3 tbl melted butter (brush on top before n after cooking)

Roll out the dough. Should make 10 3" round biscuits.

Bake at 500 for 10..12 min on foil lined pan.

#2
Always burnt, try 9 min this time.
Looks like 8 1/2 minutes would be better. Did that by accident and they didn't burn.

#3
Added 2 tsp sugar & 1 tsp vanilla. Also used "Real" cream. Don't use real cream. Too damn thick with the solids. Not "wet" enough. Had to add extra. Use the "Regular" 30% Heavy whipping cream.

500 is just too hot for this oven. Raw middles and burnt bottoms. try 425 and maybe 9..10 min.